p.d: In Hank Hoffmans first all-girl feature Kiss Me, Kristen Scott, Charlotte Stokely and Jane Wilde deliver tour def-rce performances and achieve a kind of intimacy that seems more documentary than scripted. Tristan (Kristen Scott) wants so much sl--p with women, but at the beginning of any kiss her mind and body cause a kind of self-sabotage and she disappears into herself. Enter LGBTQ sisters in arms Jenny (Charlotte Stokely) a vlogger, and Lily (Jane Wilde) her business partner and best friend. As the three discuss sexuality Tristans boundaries are pushed and played with. In the end Tristan and Jenny are face to face...Kiss Me!
